Yad Vashem’s Arab Blinders

Let’s give two cheers to Yad Vashem, Israel’s respected Holocaust memorial, for recently bestowing its "Righteous among the Nations" award on the late Egyptian physician Mohamed Helmy. With the honor, the organization for the first time recognized an Arab for saving Jews from the Nazis.
